# Intuition
Trying brute force approaches ie traversing all the numbers is not possible as the range of numbers is 10^9. And definitely it will give TLE.

Also even if we get the numbers to append, we cannot traverse them all to calculate their sum.

# Approach
Here main concept is using the formula ((n)*(n+1))/2 and to get the lowest possible numbers that do not occur in array

1. We can sort the array 
2. We must attempt to take numbers that are in between consecutive elements of the given array
3. thereby we will calculate their sum and also reduce the value of k.

We will do this process till either we make our k=0 or we have traversed the whole array.

If suppose k!=0 and we have scanned whole array then simply we have to take numbers just bigger than the last element of the array.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
Major complexity will in sorting the array so O(NlogN)
N is size of given array.

- Space complexity:
We have stored nothing so O(1).


**Please like if this post was helpful to you**

# Code
```
class Solution
{
public:
    long long minimalKSum(vector<int> &nums, int k)
    {
        long long sum = 0, num = 0;
        int ind = 0;
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());

        while (k > 0 && ind < nums.size())
        {

            long long n = nums[ind] - num - 1;
            if (n >= 0)
            {
                long long a;
                if (k >= n)  // if k>=n we will take whole n
                {
                    k = k - n;
                    a = nums[ind] - 1;
                }

                else if (k < n)  // if k<n , then we only take required value of k
                {
                    a = num + k;
                    k = 0;
                }

                if (a >= num) 
                {
                    // here we want sum of elements in between a and num
                    sum += ((a * (a + 1)) / 2) - ((num * (num + 1)) / 2);
                }
            }

            num = nums[ind];
            ind++;
        }

        // this will be useful when we have traversed whole array
        long long a = k + nums.back();
        long long last = nums.back();

        sum += ((a * (a + 1)) / 2) - ((last * (last + 1)) / 2);

        return sum;
    }
};

