solutions.content:
Sort and filter number in [1, k], and then use math

The trick part:
**If found one in [1, k], we should increase k, as we need more to fill the taken number**

Time: O(N*log(N))
Space: O(1)

```
class No2195Solution {
  public long minimalKSum(int[] nums, int k) {
    // sum of number(which means belong [1, k]) in origin array
    long taken = 0;
    Arrays.sort(nums);
    // remember last number to avoid duplicated number
    int last = 0;
    for (int num : nums) {
      if (num <= k) {
        // detect duplicate number
        if (num != last) {
          // found one in [1, k], so we increase k, as we need more to fill the taken number
          k++;
          taken += num;
        }
      } else {
        // k > num
        break;
      }

      last = num;
    }

    return (long) (k + 1) * k / 2 - taken;
  }
}
```

