**OBSERVATION:**
* As we have to make the sum of k integers minimum, it will be beneficial to us if we take as small as possible k  elements and at the same time those chosen small k elements should not be present in given array.
* For achieving above thing, I can do 3 things very intutively to get safe from TLE

i)- I can take elements from 1 to (smallest-1) value present in given array. Let's say their count is x. Now we have to take k-x elements more. How can we take those more elements?

ii)- Now to take k-x elements, we will take as many possible values I can take between two give elements in array (subject to condition that , difference between those two adjacent digits must be >0). For this step **Your input array must be sorted**

  Lets take an exmaple:
	 nums: [5,8,10] k=9  I have to take 9 smallest values which are not present in nums
	 -> By following step 1, I can take elements from 1 to 4 as they will not be present in our array
	 -> Now , we have to get 9-4 i.e 5 more values
	 -> We can now , take 2 values(6,7) wich are present between 5 and 8 (first 2 elements).
	 -> Now we have to take 5-2 i.e 3 more values
	 -> We can take 1 value (9) present between 8 and 10
	 -> Now we have to take 3-1 i.e 2 more value

 Now as we are not left for any more values in given array , we will take rest 2 smallest values beyond 10(Last element of array), those values are 11 and 12
iii) So this is only our third step , we can take rest remaining values which are beyond largest value present in array


**NOTE : For taking, first few possible smallest values from1 to( minimum_ele-1) , I have inserted 0.
For taking values beyond largest element, I have inserted 10^9 at last position**





