There are three steps involved to solve this question
Step-1: At first intialize the sum as k*(k+1)/2
Step-2: Now traverse through the array and if you find any element which has previously been included in the sum, substract it and add the next new number.
Step-3: Inorder to keep track of the numbers already included, I kept a variable (e)
At first e is intialized to k which means at first it will check whether the element in nums array is less than k then remove it from sum and add e+1 to sum. Now after doing this increament e and repeat step-2 and step-3

Below in the code the purpose of first if statement is to skip the duplicate elements in the array

