# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
we need to add unique **k** integers that results in minimum sum of the elements in the given array.here's is the breakdown of the approach:
1. The minimum sum would be of first k integers.
2. but some of the element might present in the array already.
3. so count that number and add them starting from **k+1**.
4. i have used tree set because it stores elements in sorting order,faster storing.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:`O(n log n + k log n)`.
