# Approach
We create two empty vectors, ans1 and ans2, to store the answer. We also create two unordered sets, s1 and s2, to store the unique elements of nums1 and nums2 respectively.

We then loop through each element in s1 and check if it is not present in s2. If it is not, we add it to ans1.

Similarly, we loop through each element in s2 and check if it is not present in s1. If it is not, we add it to ans2.

Finally, we return a vector containing ans1 and ans2.



# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> findDifference(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2) {
        vector<int> ans1, ans2;
        unordered_set<int> s1(nums1.begin(), nums1.end());
        unordered_set<int> s2(nums2.begin(), nums2.end());

        for (auto num : s1) {
            if (s2.find(num) == s2.end()) {
                ans1.push_back(num);
            }
        }

        for (auto num : s2) {
            if (s1.find(num) == s1.end()) {
                ans2.push_back(num);
            }
        }

        return {ans1, ans2};
    }
};

```

