- Initialize a 2D vector ans to store the result.
- Create two sets s1 and s2 from the input arrays nums1 and nums2, respectively. This removes any duplicate elements from the input arrays.
- Iterate over the elements of set s1 and check if each element is present in set s2 using the count function. If an element is not present in set s2, add it to the first vector of the result vector ans.
- Similarly, iterate over the elements of set s2 and check if each element is present in set s1. If an element is not present in set s1, add it to the second vector of the result vector ans.
- Return the result vector ans.

